node.text: I wanted to give you a behind the scenes look at one of my dance classes. This one was completely different than anything I’ve ever taught to and is a personal favorite because everyone really brought the emotion and intention…and what better song to use than “good 4 u.”  Thank you to all the dancers for trusting me and committing to this choreography ♥️

node.title: Behind the Olivia Rodrigo Dance Class

node.text:
If I told my 10 year old self this was gonna happen, I woulda slapped myself and said, “stop daydreaming and get back to work.” It’s crazy to look back at how many different things I’ve done because I still feel like I’m just getting started. I just genuinely hope some young creative is watching this and thinking, “Wow, if Kyle could do it, then I can do it,” so if that’s you, keep pushing. There’s going to be many obstacles and failures along the way but I promise you it’ll be worth it. Remember, the only difference between being defeated and inspired is perspective. I love you guys and thank you for all your support. I truly wouldn’t be here without it.

Thank you @goodmorningamerica @nidhisingh_

node.text:
TO THE BROADWAY COMMUNITY: I know times are difficult and the industry has been hit harder than most people will ever understand. When Toby, Lucy and I started collaborating on this, we wanted to do something to raise spirits and give hope with everything going on in the world, which is what Broadway has always done for me. Every time I've watched a show, I've left the theatre inspired, ready to create magic and most importantly, wanting to inspire others and leave the world a little better off than when I entered it. I'm confident things will come back stronger than ever, and I am excited to be a part of it.

To help create change, I am raising money for Broadway Cares, a non-profit that helps to provide groceries, medication, health care and hope to those struggling during this pandemic. You'll be helping someone who literally doesn't know if they'll have food next week or how they'll pay rent next month. If you are able to donate, please click the link in my bio. If not, I hope this video puts a smile on your face. As always, I am grateful for you guys. I love you.

____________________________

From the minds of KYLE HANAGAMI (director/choreographer) and TOBY MARLOW & LUCY MOSS (writers/composers of SIX on Broadway), comes the romantic comedy musical, "STAY INSIDE" starring KEVIN MCHALE (Glee) and introducing HALEY FITZGERALD.

node.text:
I’m so excited to announce my first ever online dance class, where I share everything I’ve learned as a teacher and a choreographer throughout the years. This class focuses on helping you strengthen fundamental elements, learn new pieces of choreography, discover your unique style and so much more. I’m so proud of what we've created for you. 

I structured this immersive, 30-day dance class to ensure everyone can benefit. Whether you’re new to dance or you’re a professional, this class helps you become a more confident and well-rounded dancer. 

Go to www.KyleHanagami.com to sign up now! Enrollment opens for the next session soon. Start the new year off dancing! I’ll see you in class!

node.text:
Honestly, this has been a very crazy year for everyone. On top of everything, my grandma suffered a stroke a few weeks ago and I didn’t know how to deal with it. Sometimes it’s easier for me to let my feelings out through my art. This one is for my grandparents. I hope I make them proud and I hope they dance together forever.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Kyle Hanagami on July 01, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Trying to find the words to express how proud I am of you @nowunited. You have each grown so much and in your own ways. You are better versions of yourselves and I couldn’t be happier. I love you. 

We just had our first live show in over a year at the Louvre!

node.text: When I heard GOOD 4 U by @oliviarodrigo, I knew I didn’t want to do a traditional class. I envisioned a partner piece where a a couple had broken up and one of them had moved on and the other was clearly trying to hide the fact that they were a total wreck. It’s a situation we all know a little too well. The goal was to start the piece with @haleyfitzgerald being angry because I moved on so quickly but throughout the piece I wanted to show a shift in the power dynamic so that by the end, she was the one with all the power. Just a little bit of what goes through my head when I’m choreographing. ♥️ love u guys and thanks for the support. 🙂

node.text:
What was the last time you were vulnerable? I’m realizing more and more that what I put out online and the victories I post are not an accurate representation of my life. But perfection is part of the industry I live and work in: use the best take in a music video, hire the best dancers, pick the perfect thumbnail for YouTube. In the entertainment industry, there’s little room for mistakes. However in my real life, I second guess a lot of my ideas, things don’t work out the way I see them sometimes and I convince myself that a lot of things are impossible.  
So I asked myself, how do you put that into an instagram picture, much less a piece of art? I wanted to create something about being vulnerable, even when you’re not ready to be. Being honest with others is scary but being honest with yourself is even scarier at times. But it’s also a beautiful thing. So let me ask you again, what was the last time you were vulnerable?

Directed and Choreographed by me

node.text: My grandpa was born and raised on this island and it’s my first time ever visiting.  I don’t know if you’ve ever been to where you grandparents were born but it gave me this weird feeling that’s hard to describe. It was kind of like getting a warm hug when you’re cold. Does anyone know what I’m talking about?
